<paragraph id="8BA783727144FFB1FC9E9AC4CFC6BC4B" blockId="45.[806,1421,507,773]" pageId="45" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis id="B96C5F607144FFB1FC9E9AC4C9EBBD5E" box="[806,932,507,528]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="529">Comments:</emphasis>
We consider 
<taxonomicName id="4C18F8F17144FFB1FBF59AC4CF66BD5E" authorityName="Townsend IV" authorityYear="1956" box="[1101,1321,507,528]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Capperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insomnis">
<emphasis id="B96C5F607144FFB1FBF59AC4CF66BD5E" box="[1101,1321,507,528]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="529">Capperia insomnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C18F8F17144FFB1FBAA9925CEB2BD60" authorityName="Arenberger" authorityYear="2002" box="[1042,1277,537,559]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Procapperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hackeri">
<emphasis id="B96C5F607144FFB1FBAA9925CEB2BD60" box="[1042,1277,537,559]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="529">Procapperia hackeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These two species are very close to each other in the wing pattern and characteristics. The presence of a pair of hair tufts in the middle part of the ventral side of the specialized eighth sternite of males can be considered as an autapomorphy for 
<taxonomicName id="4C18F8F17144FFB1FBF1998CCE9CBD86" authorityName="Townsend IV" authorityYear="1956" box="[1097,1235,691,712]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Capperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insomnis">
<emphasis id="B96C5F607144FFB1FBF1998CCE9CBD86" box="[1097,1235,691,712]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="529">C. insomnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is different from all known 
<taxonomicName id="4C18F8F17144FFB1FBCD99EDCF2DBDA9" box="[1141,1378,721,743]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Procapperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B96C5F607144FFB1FBCD99EDCEB1BDA9" box="[1141,1278,722,743]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="529">Procapperia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in several characters and even host plants (see above).
</paragraph>
